22/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador to BiH Douglas McElhaney held a meeting Thursday (December 21st) with the leaders of three main parties in BiH -- Milorad Dodik from the Serb Union of Independent Social Democrats, Sulejman Tihic from the Party of Democratic Action and Zlatko Lagumdzij from the Social Democratic Party -- urging them again to reach a consensus regarding the state-level government. After the talks, McElhaney described the meeting as fruitful. All parties, he said, agreed it was high time for the state-level cabinet to be formed. Elections were held on October 1st. (Dnevni Avaz - 22/12/06; RTRS, Fena, PBS - 21/12/06)
